We use the mean Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain (mean nDCG) [Jrvelin2002CumulatedGE] as the evaluation metric. A similar performance trend to the F1 metric is observed among our methods. HERB performs the best with an average nDCG score of {{2111.13611_FO0097||FO}} across relations, while BERT and Heu+TFIDF have {{2111.13611_FO0098||FO}} and {{2111.13611_FO0099||FO}}, respectively.